Articles.Content:
I've had a 1.1.3 save for a while now and just recently for no known reason whatsoever certain parts will no longer load in both the part menu and in the editor. Thoughts?

Also, the basics:

Output- https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B0GVLJwOLVGyTWtNMkZzREx4azQ/view?usp=sharing

Setup-1.5Ghz APU, 4GB Ram.

KSP x64 1.1.3.

Mods-

 

Thanks for the help (mods mostly downloaded via CKAN).

@ZooNamedGames maybe you accidentaly updated the Bahamuto Animation Modules while installing/updating another mod? Or as a dependency of another mod?

Hmm, the weird thing is that the log does not indicate any part compilation failures. So, let's trace your last steps. Did you open CKAN before you noted that behavior?

2 hours ago, Phineas Freak said:

Hmm, the weird thing is that the log does not indicate any part compilation failures. So, let's trace your last steps. Did you open CKAN before you noted that behavior?

Not that I'm aware of... should I update all mods?

For RSS/RO-RP-0 definitely not! You will break it completely.

OK, you can probably do a binary mod search (half mods removed then test, if negative then remove the other half and retest etc) until you find the problematic mod.
